greatest common divisor of two numbers read from stdin
solved entirely by recursion using the euclidean algorithm

710 = & (0, 1) => (2) {
    ? (1 == @0) {
        2 = 0                  the second number is zero so the first is the answer
    } ??? {
        2 = $710 (1, 0 % 1)    otherwise recurse with the second number and the remainder
    }
}

700 <<
$710 (700, 701) >>
